definition: to return/to go back to/to give back to/(of a responsibility) to be taken care of by/to belong to/to gather together/(used between two identical verbs) despite/to marry (of a woman) (old)/division on the abacus with a one-digit divisor

sentences.english: Ultimately, sequence diagrams are maps of interaction.
sentences.chinese: 归根结底，序列图就是交互图。

sentences.english: Bottomline is that China story is over.
sentences.chinese: 归根结底是，中国故事已经结束了。

sentences.english: THE conventional wisdom about southern politics is that it all comes down to race.
sentences.chinese: 根据一般常识，南部地区政治归根结底与种族有关。

sentences.english: The more liquid a market, after all, the more smoothly it should function.
sentences.chinese: 归根结底，市场流动性越好，其运行也就应该越顺畅。

sentences.english: But that's, after all, what we've just described, in imagining the cycling with the memory loss.
sentences.chinese: 归根结底，那正是我们对，想象中的循环失忆的描述。

sentences.english: In the final analysis, most of life's joys are transitory.
sentences.chinese: 归根结底，尘世间的欢乐大多是过眼烟云，转瞬即逝。

sentences.english: And that, in the end, is why we need open source.
sentences.chinese: 而归根结底，这就是我们需要开源的理由。

sentences.english: But in the end, there are no excuses.
sentences.chinese: 但归根结底，是没有任何借口的。

sentences.english: At its core, the American dream is childlike, too.
sentences.chinese: 归根结底，美国梦就如同孩子一样天真。

sentences.english: So in the end, being able to raise the co-financing capital is critical.
sentences.chinese: 所以，归根结底，能够筹集联合融资资金非常关键。

sentences.english: The idea essentially is to empower music fans to become A&R's.
sentences.chinese: 这个想法归根结底就是让粉丝们变身音乐制作人。

sentences.english: Apple hasn't lost the smart-phone battle by any means.
sentences.chinese: 苹果归根结底没有输掉智能手机的战斗。

sentences.english: Wavers, a candle's shadow, at the end.
sentences.chinese: 归根结底，就象蜡烛光的影子。

sentences.english: That, after all, is the unique genius of America.
sentences.chinese: 归根结底，这是美国独一无二的天赋。

sentences.english: The worth of a state, in the long run, is the worth of the individuals composing it.
sentences.chinese: 归根结底，国家的价值就是组成它的个人的价值。

sentences.english: Ultimately, end-users must deal with numerous false positives.
sentences.chinese: 归根结底，最终用户必须处理许多误报。

definition: to trace something to its source (idiom)
ultimately/in the final analysis/after all/when all is said and done
to sum up/to conclude/in a nutshell/the end (of a story)
